There were heated exchanges at the state capture inquiry. JOHANNESBURG - Things got heated at the state capture inquiry when Advocate Dali Mpofu refused to be interrupted by Pravin Gordhan's counsel. It was round two of Tom Moyane's cross-examination of Gordhan, led by Mpofu. READ: State capture inquiry: Mantashe says cameras installed by Leshabane But Justice Raymond Zondo reminded everyone who is in charge and was able to calm the tension.